    "rationale": "Six of seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required Gradation levels at MRL 2. The primary hemolysis output comparison (NRMSE 8.3 %) satisfies the quantitative acceptance criterion, and the RHI values at all five operating points satisfy RH < 1. The relevance-of-validation-activities factor achieves only Gradation 1 against a Gradation 2 requirement due to the use of a steady-state PIV comparator in a COU that specifies pulsatile inflow; this shortfall is noted as a residual uncertainty but is accepted by the team on the basis that the hemolysis scalar comparison itself is conducted under representative steady operating points bracketing the pulsatile mean flow. The primary validation result object does not carry a comparedAgainst link; the team accepts this on the basis of the narrative citation but acknowledges the formal evidentiary gap. Overall credibility is judged sufficient for a Medium assurance level, Class II device at MRL 2.",
